consensus text: 1. To ascertain if perfectly pure metals
can be made to act as galvanic
is side is oxydating & the other side
sol[superscript]n[/superscript] of sulphure - as silver does -
& oxydating in some of their points &
when prevented from oxydating in others
by sol[superscript]n[/superscript] of sulphure have the oxydating base
in the side exposed to sol[superscript]n[/superscript] of sulphure
as was the case with Silver & copper
